      "text": "Hi Monica,\n\nThanks again for reaching out about your wedding on June 12, 2027.\nBased on the details I have so far, here are a few ballpark options from Comeketo Catering.\nI used our Comeketo food calculator as the starting point so these numbers stay grounded in the same pricing logic we use internally.\nYou can also take a look here: Comeketo Catering Interactive Menu and Price Calculator\nhttps://rawdre.github.io/comeketo-menu-landing/#packages\n\nThese are ballpark numbers so I can point you in the right direction without leading you the wrong way before we lock in your final guest count, menu, and service details.\n\nTier 1\n2 meats, 3 sides, and 1 salad\nBase food price: $36.90 per person\n\nTier 1 (150 guests)\nFood: $36.90 x 150 = $5535.00\nAppetizers: $0.00 x 150 = $0.00\nMA Tax (7%): $387.45\nService, Fuel & Admin (24%): $1328.40\nService Charge (over 50 guests at $3/pp): $450.00\nBallpark Total: ~$7700.85\n\nTier 2\n3 meats, 3 sides, and 1 salad\nBase food price: $41.90 per person\n\nTier 2 (150 guests)\nFood: $41.90 x 150 = $6285.00\nAppetizers: $0.00 x 150 = $0.00\nMA Tax (7%): $439.95\nService, Fuel & Admin (24%): $1508.40\nService Charge (over 50 guests at $3/pp): $450.00\nBallpark Total: ~$8683.35\n\nFor the meats, our default steak is Top Sirloin and our default chicken is Chicken Wrapped in Bacon.\nComplimentary cookies are included.\n\nWhich option feels closer to what you want for the event?\nIf it helps, we could also jump on a quick call at 10:00 AM, 11:00 AM, or 1:00 PM.\nOnce you tell me the guest count you expect to land on and which direction feels right, I can tighten this ballpark into the right next version for you.\nFrom our call, what stood out to me is that you are not looking for a traditional plated setup. It sounds like you are leaning more toward a free-flow, hand-held food direction for the waterfront venue, which gives us a better starting point.\n\nJust so I understand, are you still trying to narrow down the food style itself, or is the bigger question now how to structure the flow for 150 guests without it feeling too formal?\n\nIf it helps, the cleanest next step is a quick call so we can tighten the service direction first and then decide which tasting date makes the most sense for you: Sunday, May 3 at 5:30 PM, Sunday, May 17 at 2:00 PM, or Sunday, May 31 at 2:00 PM.\n\nIf a quick call is easier, I can make time at 10:00 AM, 11:00 AM, or 1:00 PM.\nWhich one feels like the right next move for you?\n\nCome Taste It First\nDate options: Sunday, May 3 at 5:30 PM | Sunday, May 17 at 2:00 PM | Sunday, May 31 at 2:00 PM\nLocation: 199 Main St, Fitchburg, MA 01420\nCode: ANDRE\nTasting Preview: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1V2glKcSbQUtDes3Cuk7Q4bFPiazU1NwT/view\nTasting Registration: https://form.jotform.com/260145767354461\n\n-----\nRegards,\nAndre Raw\n​​Catering Event Coordinator\n📲 C: (978) 235-3791\n📲 W: (978) 381-1212\nFacebook | Instagram | Website"
    }
